                           <desc> </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the main hand or in a very similar hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tamallas-signs, in the shape of a cross, indicating the
                           place where the omissions, written in the margins, belong: <locus target="#5r">5r</locus> l.7, 11r l.11, 15v l.7, 22r l.20, 44v l.17,
                           52v l.1, 62r l.22, 81r l.3, 83v l.12, 103r l.14. ;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">- Omitted letters inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#13v">13v</locus>, 20v, 32r, 59v, 64r, 75r. ; </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">- Omissions inserted in small script interlineally or at
                           the end of the line, in different secondary hands: e.g., <locus target="#9v">9v</locus>, 23v, 29r, 31r, 55r, 75v, 90v, 106r, 115v.
                           ;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">- Corrections written over erased words and passages, in
                           different secondary hands: e.g., <locus target="#11r">11r</locus>, 14v,
                           17r, 18v, 23rv, 25r, 35r, 53v, 71v, 74r, 77v, 92r, 98r, 112rv, 113r,
                           127r. ; </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">- Erasures: e.g., <locus target="#22r">22r</locus>, 25v,
                           29v, 109v, 110r, 119rv, 123r, 125v, 145rab. ;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">- Excerpt from P<locus target="#117">117</locus> written
                           on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>. ; </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">- Doxology written in red, in a secondary hand: <locus target="#141v">141v</locus>. ;</item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">- Some names, e.g., Gǝrimā Garazihar, ʾAbrǝhā Garazihar,
